    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love the photograph.  Really elegant.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-11630' data-commentid="11630" data-postid="1036" data-belowelement="comment-11630" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Julie Erwin" aria-label='Reply to Julie Erwin'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-11631" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/01/squirrel-it-away/#comment-11631"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-02-27T05:46:00-05:00">Friday, February 27, 2009 at 5:46 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>hooray for peanut butter and jelly.  I have found that when i crave old faithful pbj but push it aside because it&#8217;s common, easy and maybe too &#8230;. i just end up eating two at a time later.  pbj is just a perfect food, particularly when toasted up so the outside gets crisp and the insides melt together&#8230;. so although good for you for giving up store-bought sliced bread, i think peanut butter and jelly sandwiches should always be relished and enjoyed to the full.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-11631' data-commentid="11631" data-postid="1036" data-belowelement="comment-11631" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-11632" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/04225535216850178185" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Emily</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2009/01/squirrel-it-away/#comment-11632"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2009-03-02T11:19:00-05:00">Monday, March 2, 2009 at 11:19 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Made this the night before last with my friend here in her tiny kitchen in Rennes.  It was delicious, though I did add a bit more stock that it called for because it was a bit too creamy for me and my annoyingly delicate stomach (for all things deep-fried and cream-filled).</>However, I do have to ask how in the heck you managed to serve 4 people with this!  I mean, we gobbled down the entire pot between the two of us, and that was with salad and sanglier saucisson.  Apparently, I eat too much 😉</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-11632' data-commentid="11632" data-postid="1036" data-belowelement="comment-11632" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Emily" aria-label='Reply to Emily'>Reply</a>    </div>
